Create a complete GitHub Actions workflow that automatically generates Pull Request documentation using AI.

Requirements:

1. Trigger
- Run on pull_request events:
  - opened
  - synchronize
  - reopened
  - ready_for_review
- Do not run for draft PRs.

2. PR Analysis
- Collect all changed files from the PR using GitHub API.
- Exclude CHANGELOG.md from analysis.
- Retrieve:
  - filename
  - status
  - additions
  - deletions
  - patch/diff content
- Build statistics:
  - total files changed
  - total additions
  - total deletions
  - frontend files
  - backend files
  - config files
  - test files
  - style files

3. AI Documentation Generation
- Use GitHub Models endpoint:
  https://models.github.ai/inference/chat/completions
- Use model:
  openai/gpt-4.1

- Send the actual PR diff to the model.
- The AI must generate:
  {
    "pr_description": "...",
    "changelog": "..."
  }

4. PR Description Requirements

Generate a detailed human-readable document intended for:

- Developers
- Reviewers
- Technical Leads
- Project Managers

Use exactly these sections:

## Summary
Explain:
- what changed
- why it changed
- business purpose
- technical purpose

## What Changed
Describe changes step by step in natural language.

Group changes by:
- feature
- screen
- component
- service
- state management
- API
- configuration
- testing

## Application Impact
Explain:
- affected areas
- user impact
- developer impact

## Technical Details
Describe:
- architecture changes
- data flow changes
- state management changes
- helper functions
- reusable components
- filtering logic
- transformations
- validations

## Testing
Provide concrete manual testing steps.

## Risks and Review Notes
Describe:
- edge cases
- regressions
- risks
- reviewer focus areas

5. Writing Style

The generated content must:
- be written in natural English
- sound like a senior engineer wrote it
- avoid generic statements
- avoid simply listing files
- explain behavior and intent
- explain business value
- explain technical impact
- be understandable by non-developers

6. Changelog Requirements

Generate:

### Added
### Changed
### Testing
### Review Notes

The changelog must be developer-friendly and detailed.

7. Fallback Logic

If the AI request fails:
- generate a fallback PR description
- generate a fallback changelog
- never fail the workflow

8. PR Update

Automatically update the Pull Request description with the generated documentation.

9. CHANGELOG.md Management

Implement changelog preservation logic:

- Maintain full changelog history.
- Each PR entry must be wrapped with markers:

<!-- PR-123-CHANGELOG-START -->
...
<!-- PR-123-CHANGELOG-END -->

- If the workflow runs again for the same PR:
  replace the existing entry instead of creating duplicates.

- If the PR does not exist in the changelog:
  insert a new entry at the top.

- Preserve all previous changelog entries.

10. Git Operations

Commit and push CHANGELOG.md automatically back to the PR branch.

11. Final PR Comment

Add a summary comment containing:
- files changed
- additions/deletions
- changelog updated

12. Output

Generate the COMPLETE workflow file.

Return only the final YAML workflow.
Do not return explanations.
